WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:25.000
Blue Fins by Sarah Axton

00:25.000 --> 00:29.000
It's hot. The sun is shining.

00:29.000 --> 00:32.000
The sky is blue.

00:33.000 --> 00:37.000
The hot sun is shining in the blue sky.

00:38.000 --> 00:41.000
Jen lives in Australia.

00:42.000 --> 00:46.000
Jen and her friends are not at college today.

00:47.000 --> 00:49.000
It is the weekend.

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
Jen is on the beach.

00:53.000 --> 00:56.000
She's standing on the hot sand.

00:56.000 --> 01:00.000
She's waving to her boyfriend, Rick.

01:01.000 --> 01:04.000
Rick and Jen's friends are in the sea.

01:05.000 --> 01:08.000
They are swimming and surfing.

01:09.000 --> 01:11.000
"Hi, Rick!"

01:12.000 --> 01:14.000
Rick is very happy.

01:15.000 --> 01:17.000
He has a new surfboard.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
The surfboard is red and white.

01:22.000 --> 01:25.000
Rick's favourite sport is surfing.

01:27.000 --> 01:29.000
"I'm going surfing."

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
"My new surfboard is very fast."

01:34.000 --> 01:36.000
"It's great."

01:37.000 --> 01:39.000
"I'm going swimming."

01:40.000 --> 01:42.000
"I'm going to look at the fish underwater."

01:43.000 --> 01:45.000
"See you later."

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
Jen walks along the beach.

01:49.000 --> 01:51.000
She sits on some rocks.

01:52.000 --> 01:56.000
Jen puts her blue rubber fins on her feet.

01:57.000 --> 02:02.000
She puts the yellow mask and snorkel on her face.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.000
The water is warm.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
Her blue fins splash loudly.

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
Jen takes a big breath.

02:13.000 --> 02:16.000
She dives under the water.

02:17.000 --> 02:22.000
She moves her blue fins and swims very quickly.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
She goes down and down.

02:27.000 --> 02:30.000
She can see fish and plants.

02:31.000 --> 02:36.000
She can see fish and plants through her yellow mask.

02:37.000 --> 02:41.000
The fish and plants are very beautiful.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
The fish swim all around her.

02:45.000 --> 02:48.000
Jen can see yellow fish.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
She can see blue fish.

02:52.000 --> 02:56.000
There are green, red and white fish.

02:57.000 --> 03:00.000
Jen looks at the plants.

03:01.000 --> 03:03.000
They grow on the rocks.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.000
There are tall plants.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.000
There are small plants.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.000
Jen touches the plants.

03:15.000 --> 03:17.000
Some plants are soft.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.000
Some plants are hard.

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
Fish live in the plants and rocks.

03:27.000 --> 03:30.000
Jen sees a sea urchin.

03:31.000 --> 03:34.000
She doesn't touch the sea urchin.

03:34.000 --> 03:37.000
[повтор строки удален]

03:38.000 --> 03:40.000
It's dangerous.

03:41.000 --> 03:44.000
It has sharp spines.

03:45.000 --> 03:48.000
Jen swims up to get air.

03:49.000 --> 03:52.000
Her snorkel comes out of the water.

03:53.000 --> 03:56.000
Jen takes a big breath.

03:57.000 --> 04:01.000
She dives down under the water again.

04:02.000 --> 04:06.000
Jen swims past a large rock.

04:07.000 --> 04:10.000
Suddenly she stops.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
She sees a dolphin.

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
It cannot swim.

04:17.000 --> 04:20.000
The dolphin is in a net.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.000
The net is around the dolphin's body.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.000
The net is around the rocks.

04:30.000 --> 04:34.000
The dolphin cannot swim up to get air.

04:35.000 --> 04:39.000
The beautiful blue dolphin is dying.

04:41.000 --> 04:44.000
The dolphin moves its fins slowly.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
But the net is strong.

04:48.000 --> 04:51.000
The dolphin cannot break the net.

04:54.000 --> 04:57.000
"Hi, dolphin. I'll help you."

04:58.000 --> 05:01.000
Jen pulls the net from the rocks.

05:02.000 --> 05:05.000
She pulls the net from the dolphin.

05:06.000 --> 05:09.000
The dolphin is out of the net.

05:10.000 --> 05:13.000
The dolphin moves its fins quickly.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.000
It swims fast.

05:17.000 --> 05:20.000
The dolphin swims up and up.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
It takes a breath of air.

05:24.000 --> 05:27.000
The dolphin looks down at Jen.

05:28.000 --> 05:30.000
Then it swims away.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
Jen is happy.

05:36.000 --> 05:39.000
She tells Rick about the dolphin.

05:43.000 --> 05:46.000
Next day, everybody is swimming.

05:46.000 --> 05:48.000
No one is surfing.

05:49.000 --> 05:51.000
The sea is flat.

05:51.000 --> 05:54.000
The sun is high in the sky.

05:55.000 --> 05:59.000
The hot sun shines on the water.

06:00.000 --> 06:03.000
The water is silver and blue.

06:04.000 --> 06:09.000
Men, women and children are in the sea.

06:10.000 --> 06:13.000
They are playing and laughing.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
Everybody is happy.

06:17.000 --> 06:20.000
The lifeguard watches the sea.

06:21.000 --> 06:24.000
He looks at the people swimming.

06:25.000 --> 06:28.000
Suddenly he shouts loudly.

06:29.000 --> 06:34.000
"Shark! Quick! Get out of the water!"

06:35.000 --> 06:38.000
The shark is swimming quickly.

06:39.000 --> 06:40.000
It is hungry.

06:41.000 --> 06:44.000
Its black fin is above the water.

06:45.000 --> 06:49.000
The shark is swimming towards the people.

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
Everybody is frightened.

06:53.000 --> 06:55.000
Sharks are dangerous.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
They have long, sharp teeth.

06:59.000 --> 07:03.000
Everybody swims towards the beach.

07:04.000 --> 07:09.000
Jen and Rick are swimming a long way from the beach.

07:10.000 --> 07:13.000
The shark comes towards Rick.

07:14.000 --> 07:16.000
Jen is very frightened.

07:16.000 --> 07:18.000
She shouts at Rick.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.000
"Rick! Look out!"

07:22.000 --> 07:27.000
Rick sees the shark's black fin above the water.

07:28.000 --> 07:31.000
The shark is 30 meters away.

07:32.000 --> 07:36.000
Jen and Rick swim towards the beach.

07:37.000 --> 07:41.000
Now the shark is 15 meters away.

07:42.000 --> 07:47.000
Jen can see the shark's sharp white teeth.

07:48.000 --> 07:52.000
Suddenly they see another fin in the water.

07:53.000 --> 07:54.000
A blue fin.

07:55.000 --> 07:57.000
It is a dolphin.

07:58.000 --> 08:01.000
It is the beautiful blue dolphin.

08:02.000 --> 08:06.000
The dolphin is swimming towards the shark.

08:07.000 --> 08:09.000
The dolphin hits the shark.

08:10.000 --> 08:15.000
The dolphin hits the shark again and again.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.000
The shark swims away.

08:19.000 --> 08:22.000
Rick and Jen are safe.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.000
"Look, Rick!"

08:26.000 --> 08:28.000
"It's my blue dolphin."

08:29.000 --> 08:30.000
"Thanks, dolphin."

08:31.000 --> 08:33.000
"Thanks for saving us."

